%N A395037 Number of relations on an n-set that are not transitive.
%F A395037 a(n) = 2^(n^2) - A006905(n).
%e A395037 a(2) = 3 because on the 2-set X={1,2}, the only relations that are not transitive are {(1,2),(2,1)}, {(1,2),(2,1),(1,1)} and {(1,2),(2,1),(2,2)}.
